theorem Topology.closureSubsetClosure_of_subset_interiorClosure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (h : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (B : Set X))) :
    closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := by
  -- First, upgrade the given inclusion to one into `closure B`.
  have hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := by
    intro x hxA
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior (closure (B : Set X)) := h hxA
    exact (interior_subset : interior (closure (B : Set X)) ⊆ closure (B : Set X)) hxInt
  -- Monotonicity of `closure` gives the desired inclusion.
  exact closure_mono hAB
